Peter Okoye, one of the famous singing twin brothers, Psquare, has narrated how he and his family once experienced poverty. Mr P told Tv host, Nancy Isime, why he fears poverty the most.   Otobo renews battle with Apostle Suleman, releases amorous…     I may die soon, says Elon Musk     How to become a good cross dresser, by Bobrisky   Asked to name his biggest fear, Mr P said: “I’m not afraid of death, the only thing I’m afraid of in this life is poverty and being broke. “I’ve tasted it before. I’ve been in our house and a bulldozer came to demolish it while we were still living there with my parents, six boys and two girls living in a one-bedroom apartment. They had to divide the room with a curtain. “The landlord had sold the property and we were still begging to give us some time to get somewhere else and the next thing was the bulldozer coming to demolish the house while we were still living there.”